.TH "snd_card_rw_proc_new" 9 "snd_card_rw_proc_new" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_card_rw_proc_new \- Create a read/write text proc file entry for the card
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_card_rw_proc_new
.BI "(struct snd_card *card "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "void *private_data "  ","
.BI "void (*read)(struct snd_info_entry *, struct snd_info_buffer *) "  ","
.BI "void (*write)(struct snd_info_entry *entry, struct snd_info_buffer *buffer) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "card" 12
the card instance
.IP "name" 12
the file name
.IP "private_data" 12
the arbitrary private data
.IP "read" 12
the read callback
.IP "write" 12
the write callback, NULL for read-only
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This proc file entry will be registered via \fBsnd_card_register\fP call, and
it will be removed automatically at the card removal, too.
